  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I would give it up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I would run away from anything that was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] too close to commitment or taking responsibility for others for their well-being.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It became very scary type of reactions.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] What came later on, which was really a big change in my life, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I got in touch with Jehovah's Witnesses accidentally.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Now, these people impressed me very much during the war as I told you.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "As a matter of fact-- this is a little aside story.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "While I was in Landsberg, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they conducted-- the American military conducted a trial against guards of Mauthausen camps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But this was not the big shots, but the guards and people against whom there was no evidence.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They had locked-- locked them up in Dachau, form a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And now, they were looking for people who were in these camps who possibly can present evidence which can be used in the trials, just pre-trial testimony and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So, I was called there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I spent three weeks there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And, again, I ran into two witnesses who were there in the camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "This is the first time I talked to them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "One was paralyzed in the right arm.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because what they did to him trying to break him, is to hang him backwards like this, on poles was bolts between the fingers and just hanging like this.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Tied them up from the top, hanging like this for eight hours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "What they-- what they used to do in this pre-trial thing is to bring the Germans one after another on the stage.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then two Americans would interview them.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
